      <hr>
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <p>Information about the geographic coverage of the described material (usually survey
         material). This information in coded form may be contained in field 052 (Geographic
                     Classification Code).
      </p>
      <p>Sometimes displayed and/or printed with an introductory phrase that is generated as a
                     display constant based on the first indicator value.      </p>
      <hr>
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> INDICATORS
      </h4>
      <div class="indicator"><strong>First Indicator - Display constant controller</strong> <div class="description">Controls the generation of a display constant preceding the note.
            <div class="indicatorvalue"><strong># - Geographic coverage</strong> <div class="description">Used to generate the display constant <em>Geographic coverage:</em>.
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="indicatorvalue"><strong>8 - No display constant generated</strong> </div>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="indicator"><strong>Second Indicator - Undefined</strong> <div class="description">Undefined and contains a blank (#).
            </div>
      </div>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> SUBFIELD CODES
      </h4>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$a - Geographic coverage note</strong> <div class="description">Entire text of the note.</div>
         <div class="example">
            <table width="100%">
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
